<% title 'Start' %>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Apply to court about child arrangements</h1>

    <p class="govuk-body-l">
      You can use this service to apply for a court order about child arrangements. This can be for a child arrangements
      order, a prohibited steps order and a specific issue order.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      The process is different if you're applying in
      <a href="https://www.mygov.scot/crime-justice-and-the-law/courts-and-sentencing" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">Scotland</a>
      and
      <a href="https://www.nidirect.gov.uk/articles/solicitors-and-courts" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">Northern Ireland</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="govuk-inset-text">
      This service is the digital version of the C100 paper application form.
    </div>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Fees</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      The court fee is £215. Only the person applying to court (the applicant) or their solicitor needs to pay. Check if
      you can
      <a href="https://www.gov.uk/get-help-with-court-fees" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">get help
        paying the court fee</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      You can pay by credit or debit card over the phone, sending a cheque, or by cash, cheque or card in person at the
      court. If you have a solicitor representing you, they may pay the court by direct debit. You’ll need to provide
      their ‘fee account number’.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      Legal aid may be available.
      <a href="https://www.gov.uk/check-legal-aid" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">Check if you can
        get legal aid</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Before you start your application</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">Follow these steps before you start:</p>

    <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number app-list--icon-steps">
      <li>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          Look at alternative ways of resolving your dispute
        </h3>
        Read the
        <a href="https://helpwithchildarrangements.service.justice.gov.uk" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">child
          arrangements guide</a> to see if there’s a more suitable option than going to court.
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          Check if you have a valid reason for not attending a Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting
          (<abbr title="Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting">MIAM</abbr>)
        </h3>
        A <abbr title="Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting">MIAM</abbr> is an introductory meeting that
        explains how
        <a href="https://helpwithchildarrangements.service.justice.gov.uk/professional-mediation" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">mediation</a>
        can help resolve your dispute. You’re legally required to attend one if you want to go to court, unless
        <a href="/about/miam_exemptions" class="govuk-link" target="_blank">you’re exempt</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          Find a mediator and book a <abbr title="Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting">MIAM</abbr>
        </h3>
        If you have to attend a <abbr title="Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting">MIAM</abbr> you’ll need to
        <a href="https://www.familymediationcouncil.org.uk/find-local-mediator/" class="govuk-link" rel="external" target="_blank">find
          a mediator</a> to book one.
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          Get a document signed by your mediator
        </h3>
        When you attend your <abbr title="Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting">MIAM</abbr> you’ll need a
        signed document confirming this. Bring the document to your first court hearing.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">After you complete your application</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      You can submit your completed application straight to the court electronically. If you enter an email address,
      you’ll get a confirmation that it’s been sent with your application attached. You can also download, print and
      send your application by post if you prefer.
    </p>

    <%= link_to entrypoint_what_is_needed_path, class: 'govuk-button govuk-button--start govuk-!-margin-top-3', data: { module: 'govuk-button' }, role: 'button', draggable: false do %>
      Start application
      <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
        <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
      </svg>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
